Keybindings

# Modifier Chosen: <kbd>Win</kbd>

#Control the system


<kbd>Alt+<kbd>Ctrl+<kbd>r - Reboot
<kbd>Alt+<kbd>Ctrl+<kbd>s - Suspend
<kbd>Alt+<kbd>Ctrl+<kbd>x - Poweroff

#i3 functionality

##controling the wm
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>q - reload i3 configuration file
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>e - exit i3, go back to login manager
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>r - restart i3 in place

##predefined layouts
<kbd>Win+<kbd>s - activate stacking layout
<kbd>Win+<kbd>t - activate tabbed layout
<kbd>Win+<kbd>n - activate split layout

#Starting Programs
<kbd>Ctrl+<kbd>Space - start launcher (synapse)
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Return - start terminal (sakura)
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>Space - start browser (firefox)
<kbd>Win+<kbd>d - start dmenu (j4-dmenu-desktop)
<kbd>Win+<kbd>e - start filemanager (pcmanfm)

#Window ("container") modification

##Changing / Closing windows
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>c - kill active window
<kbd>Win+<kbd>b - Split in horizontal orientation
<kbd>Win+<kbd>v - Split in vertical orientation

##Layout changes
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>Space - Toggle floating / tiling 
<kbd>Win+<kbd>f - toggle fullscreen
<kbd>Win+<kbd>r - Enter resize mode
     # Pressing left will shrink the window’s width.
     # Pressing right will grow the window’s width.
     # Pressing up will shrink the window’s height.
     # Pressing down will grow the window’s height.
	 # Keeping "Win" pressed, allows resizing via mouse

	<kbd>h,<kbd>j,<kbd>k,<kbd>l - resize (shrink/grow width / height by 10x10 pixels)
	<kbd>Left Arrow, <kbd>Down Arrow, <kbd>Up Arrow, <kbd>Right Arrow - (shrink/grow width / height by 10x10 pixels)
	<kbd>Return,<kbd>Escape  - leave resize mode
	 	
##Moving open windows
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>h / <kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>Left Arrow - move focused window left
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>j / <kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>Down Arrow - move focused window down
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>k / <kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>Up Arrow - move focused window up
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>l / <kbd>Win+<kbd>Shift+<kbd>Right Arrow - move focused window right

##Navigating open windows
<kbd>Win+<kbd>h / Win+Left Arrow - change focus left
<kbd>Win+<kbd>j / Win+Down Arrow - change focus down
<kbd>Win+<kbd>k / Win-Up Arrow - change focus up
<kbd>Win+<kbd>l / Win-Right Arrow - change focus right

<kbd>Win+<kbd>a - focus parent container
<kbd>Win+<kbd>Space - toggle focus between tiling floating

#Workspace Modifications
<kbd>Win+<kbd>y - move workspace to left output
<kbd>Win+<kbd>x - move Workspace to right output
<kbd>Win+<kbd>1[-10] - change to workspace
<kbd>Win+<kbd><kbd>Shift+<kbd>1[-10] - move container to workspace















